Food and Feeding.
[.anternfish (
Myctophidae
) and cod icefish (
Nototheniidae
), cephalopodes,krill, and occasionally penguins, make up the diet of Subantarctic Fur Seals. At Amsterdam Island, they consume cephalopods,fish, and rockhopper penguins (Eudyptes chrysocome). The diet of Subantarctic Fur Seals at the Prince Edward Islands was 50% cephalopods, 45% fish, and 5% krill.
